Representative Steny Hoyer, House Democratic Whip, expressed his support for President Obama's American Jobs Act. He emphasized the need to create jobs and grow the economy, stating that everyone should have the opportunity to succeed through hard work. Hoyer mentioned the Make It In America plan, which aims to restore the manufacturing sector and provide worker training. He also highlighted the importance of reducing the deficit while creating jobs. Hoyer stated that many of the ideas in the Make It In America plan have bipartisan support and should be swiftly passed through Congress.